write a python function to read from an excel spreadsheet.
Here is the code for reading data from an Excel file in Python using the openpyxl library:
```python
import openpyxl

def read_excel(file_path):
    # Open the workbook and select the active sheet
    workbook = openpyxl.load_workbook(filename=file_path, read_only=True)
    worksheet = workbook[None]  # get the active sheet
    
    # Loop through each row in the worksheet
    for i, row in enumerate(worksheet):
        cells = [cell.value for cell in row]  # extract values from each column
        
        yield cells
```
